# 5. 始まりのぬくもり

Minori: Whew! As fun as today's shoot was, they had us do so much!
Airi: They told us that it'd be for a camping special, but chopping all that firewood was harder than I expected...
KAITO: <We actually had a lot of fun watching you though.>
Miku: <Yeah. I think the special's gonna turn out really great!>
Shizuku: Hehe. That means a lot coming from all of you.
Shizuku: Still... We really worked up a good sweat.
Shizuku: I was hoping to take a bath... Why don't we all go together?
Minori: I really wanna join you, but I still need to get my bags all sorted...
Haruka: Now that you mention it, Minori, you do have all your bags laid out...
Haruka: I've also been thinking about getting my things sorted, so I'll also join you in a little bit.
Airi: I still have a few emails left that I need to reply to, so I'll head over once I'm finished with those.
Shizuku: Okay. Then, I'll go on ahead.
Rin: <No fair! I wanna take a dip in the hot spring!>
Luka: <Yes, it would've been nice to give my skin a refreshing treatment. Is there any way for you to bring back some of the water?>
Shizuku: That may be difficult... Instead, we can bring back some manju. I'm sure you'll enjoy them very much.
Rin: <What?! You mean the ones Saito brought over yesterday?>
Rin: <Awesome! I promise to wait and be really patient♪>
MEIKO: <Oh, you. But I understand your excitement.>
Shizuku: (The baths should be... Ah, this way. Thank goodness for all these signs.)
Shizuku: (Still, this inn really is lovely... Our room feels relaxing, and the staff here are so kind...)
Shizuku: (We talked it over a little after that...)
Shizuku: (And we agreed to respect Saito's decision to help keep her family's business going.)
Shizuku: (And I...agree with that, but...)
???: You're Ms. Hinomori, correct?
Shizuku: Huh...?
???: Ah, I had a feeling. Thank you for always being so kind to my granddaughter.
Senior Proprietress: I apologize for not introducing myself sooner. I am the previous proprietress of this inn, as well as Ayaka's grandmother.
Shizuku: Her grandmother...?!
Shizuku: No, I should be the one telling you how grateful we are for all the kindness she's given us.
Senior Proprietress: Hehe. I appreciate that very much. And I'm so glad that I finally got to meet you.
Senior Proprietress: But... I suppose all the stories I'd heard were true. She really has been working with you...
Senior Proprietress: You're the reason why she decided to start working part-time at events, so it seems fate is not without a sense of humor...
Shizuku: Wait, I am...?
Senior Proprietress: Oh, did she not tell you?
Shizuku: No, I... I knew that she's been a big fan of mine for a very long time...
Shizuku: But I had no idea that she chose to start helping with events because of me.
Senior Proprietress: Oh, I see...
Senior Proprietress: If I recall... I believe it all started about three years ago.
Senior Proprietress: Something about meeting you for the first time at a meet and greet...?
Shizuku: At a meet and greet? About three years ago...?
Shizuku: Oh... That may've been the event where everyone from the third generation was introduced.
Senior Proprietress: I can't recall many details, but I do remember Ayaka making a bit of a mistake while helping out here and feeling bad about it.
Senior Proprietress: Apparently, you asked her if she was okay after noticing that something was bothering her.
Shizuku: What...?
Shizuku: Hello! Thank you for coming to see us today!
Shizuku: Oh no... Is everything okay? You seem to be feeling a little down.
Shizuku: But don't worry! I know a charm for making people smile by shaking hands with me.
Shizuku: All I have to do is...this!
Shizuku: After you release my hands, you should be able to move forward with your head held high. I hope that helps cheer you up.
Senior Proprietress: After that, she gained an interest in working as an event staff member.
Senior Proprietress: I suspect it's because she saw firsthand the power that events have to move hearts.
Shizuku: Saito...
Senior Proprietress: But I doubt she ever dreamed of having the opportunity to work with you yourself someday.
Senior Proprietress: Oh, speaking of which, you should've heard how happy she was when she called home after working on one of your group's events for the first time.
Senior Proprietress: She even kept sending us messages saying, “It's so amazing how hard she works,” and, “I'm giving MORE MORE JUMP! all the support I can!”
Senior Proprietress: But above all else, she sounded the happiest when telling us how the event she helped put together actually succeeded.
Shizuku: Oh...
Saito: After helping put on your last event, I've decided that I want to assist and support idols for a living...
Saito: I ended up having so much fun that I found myself wanting to do this for a living.
Saito: It felt like I played an actual role in helping spread hope to others like all of you. That made me feel so happy...!
Shizuku: Yes... She also told us the same thing.
Shizuku: When she told us that, it became clear that she genuinely has a passion for our line of work... Her words left me speechless.
Senior Proprietress: Ah, yes, I'd imagine so. Which is why I posed a question to her.
Senior Proprietress: If she likes it that much, then why not pursue it as a career?
Shizuku: ...!
Shizuku: How did she respond...?
Senior Proprietress: She said...
Saito: What...?
Saito: G-Grandma, what are you saying? I want to serve this inn's guests for a living!
Saito: That's why I'm going to become the next proprietress. My event staff job is just a way to build up experience.
Senior Proprietress: But you always sound so happy whenever you're talking about work.
Senior Proprietress: You don't need to worry about this inn. If there's something else that you wish to do, then I think you should pursue that.
Senior Proprietress: We care far more about your happiness than the future of this inn.
Saito: My happiness matters more...?
Senior Proprietress: Yes, so if you have a different dream in mind, then... I think you should try making it come true.
Saito: No, you've got it all wrong!
Saito: I want to become the next proprietress of this inn! I've been planning to since I was in elementary school!
Saito: So, Grandma, you don't need to worry.
Saito: After graduation, I'm coming straight back here!
Senior Proprietress: ... What I'm worried about is your...
Senior Proprietress: We kept going around in circles after that...
Senior Proprietress: But she was so adamant that I ended up saying, “It seems it really is your dream to take over.”
Senior Proprietress: However, I'm still having a hard time actually believing that...
Shizuku: So... Is her mother aware of any of this?
Senior Proprietress: No. I've taken it upon myself to hear what Ayaka has to say since her mother doesn't know much about the entertainment industry.
Senior Proprietress: Also...
Saito: Please don't tell Mom about what we just talked about, okay, Grandma?
Saito: I don't want her to worry, so... Please.
Senior Proprietress: This subject became a secret between just us after she said that...
Shizuku: A secret between the two of you...?
Senior Proprietress: However, I have a feeling that her mother would say the same thing as me.
Shizuku: What...?
Senior Proprietress: I mean, what parent doesn't want their child's dreams to come true?
Shizuku: (She's right...)
Shizuku: (Saito certainly seems to be placing the happiness of those she cares about above her own dream...)
Shizuku: (And yet, those same people want her to pursue what she wants... They believe that's what will make her the happiest.)
Shizuku: (They all care so much about each other, but... They're not on the same page at all.)
Senior Proprietress: Oh, look at the time. I'm sorry. I didn't mean to give you our whole family's story.
Senior Proprietress: You were about to take a bath, yes? Our spring's known for being both rejuvenating and good for your skin. I hope you have a soothing bath.
Shizuku: Oh...
